00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:09,440
Be careful not to hurt your hand.

292
00:12:13,039 --> 00:12:13,320
Great!

293
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:14,359
Awesome.

294
00:12:14,359 --> 00:12:14,719
Half for each.

295
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:20,096
Wait a moment.

296
00:12:20,096 --> 00:12:20,799
I'll crack it a bit more for you.

297
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:24,479
Nice.

298
00:12:25,119 --> 00:12:26,208
I've got to get the service right.

299
00:12:26,208 --> 00:12:26,840
(Thoughtful Zhuoran)
Right?

300
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:28,679
If it's not done right,
it's not done at all.

301
00:12:29,239 --> 00:12:29,919
I'll take it myself.

302
00:12:29,919 --> 00:12:30,200
Okay.

303
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,080
Thank you.

304
00:12:31,479 --> 00:12:32,320
Awesome.

305
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:35,400
Watch Mr. Dong peel a walnut kernel.

306
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,080
Smells so good.

307
00:12:47,424 --> 00:12:48,520
Do you think you've felt love

308
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:51,719
these past few days?

309
00:12:52,479 --> 00:12:53,239
Be honest.

310
00:12:53,239 --> 00:12:53,880
Honestly.

311
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:57,159
I think it's too early
to talk about love right now.

312
00:12:57,760 --> 00:12:58,280
I think so too.

313
00:12:58,960 --> 00:12:59,479
I think so too.

314
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,159
These past two days, I've been chatting

315
00:13:01,159 --> 00:13:01,719
with them in the house.

316
00:13:01,719 --> 00:13:02,200
It feels like

317
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:04,359
one day in the house
is like a year on the outside.

318
00:13:04,359 --> 00:13:04,760
That's true.

319
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:05,679
Everyone is so focused,

320
00:13:05,679 --> 00:13:07,320
spending time together, communicating,

321
00:13:07,799 --> 00:13:08,960
and showing their strengths.

322
00:13:11,679 --> 00:13:12,320
Did you burn yourself?

323
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:12,719
Yes.

324
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:15,280
I didn't realize it was that hot.

325
00:13:15,719 --> 00:13:16,280
It's okay.

326
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:16,880
Guess it's up to me then.

327
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:17,359
I'm tough as nails.

328
00:13:20,119 --> 00:13:21,200
I think it's time
to eat these dried apples

329
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,000
while they're still warm.

330
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:22,520
Here.

331
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:23,359
Pick up a piece.

332
00:13:23,359 --> 00:13:24,440
I can't let

333
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,080
your hard work go to waste.

334
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:27,200
Be careful, it's hot.

335
00:13:28,359 --> 00:13:28,960
Really delicious.

336
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:29,960
Right? Doesn't it taste like

337
00:13:30,679 --> 00:13:32,039
the one better than a dessert?

338
00:13:32,039 --> 00:13:33,559
- Yes.
- It feels flaky.

339
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:35,479
Not bad, right?

340
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:42,760
Is this an ATV?

341
00:13:43,479 --> 00:13:44,119
Take it for a spin.

342
00:13:44,679 --> 00:13:45,479
Just a quick drive. Let's go.

343
00:13:46,679 --> 00:13:47,880
Let me see if I can fit inside.

344
00:13:47,880 --> 00:13:48,679
(Staring)

345
00:13:48,679 --> 00:13:50,280
Can your legs even fit in there?

346
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:52,440
(Slightly struggling)

347
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:52,840
It's okay.

348
00:13:54,082 --> 00:13:55,719
(Easily handling it)

349
00:13:55,719 --> 00:13:57,080
Control your speed!

350
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:57,320
Go.

351
00:13:57,799 --> 00:13:58,479
I'm off.

352
00:13:58,479 --> 00:13:58,760
Go ahead.

353
00:14:01,159 --> 00:14:02,080
Go!

354
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:09,359
There you go!

355
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:15,280
Comfortable.

356
00:14:18,799 --> 00:14:20,239
This is really cool.

357
00:14:22,479 --> 00:14:24,200
I've mastered turning now!

358
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:26,200
Not bad.

359
00:14:29,679 --> 00:14:31,280
Cool. This car is so cool.

360
00:14:35,679 --> 00:14:36,520
Stop driving!

361
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:42,150
The route could be a bit longer.

362
00:14:42,150 --> 00:14:43,039
- Right?
- I think so too.

363
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:44,352
Which one is the brake?

364
00:14:44,352 --> 00:14:45,320
The left one.

365
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,599
(Almost flipped)

366
00:14:46,599 --> 00:14:48,559
It fulfilled my dream of driving fast.

367
00:14:48,559 --> 00:14:49,520
(Realized another wish)
This is pretty fast.

368
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:49,799
Awesome.

369
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:50,880
Not bad.

370
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:55,719
Shall we go play with the ATVs?

371
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:56,840
Okay.

372
00:14:59,239 --> 00:15:00,760
But I can't overtake you

373
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:02,159
if you're in front of me.

374
00:15:02,272 --> 00:15:03,616
(Rear car, front car)

375
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,119
I can't overtake you.

376
00:15:06,159 --> 00:15:06,960
Alright then.

377
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:08,159
Pull up over here.

378
00:15:08,544 --> 00:15:09,472
(Leaving space)

379
00:15:09,599 --> 00:15:11,080
You're letting me go in front of you?

380
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:11,719
Okay.

381
00:15:12,599 --> 00:15:13,119
That won't work.

382
00:15:13,119 --> 00:15:14,799
It's scarier if you overtake me.

383
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:16,679
This is so fast.

384
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,640
(Newbie on the road)

385
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:19,280
Yes, very fast.

386
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:19,760
You need to...

387
00:15:20,239 --> 00:15:21,039
Or if you think...

388
00:15:21,039 --> 00:15:21,760
Then I'm leaving. Bye.

389
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,479
(Distance growing further apart)

390
00:15:34,479 --> 00:15:36,119
I can't catch up at all.

391
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,119
This is so fast.

392
00:15:39,679 --> 00:15:42,559
I have no way to overtake you.

393
00:15:46,592 --> 00:15:48,832
(Having a blast driving)

394
00:15:50,599 --> 00:15:53,320
Be careful!

395
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:54,599
Slow down.

396
00:15:54,599 --> 00:15:56,080
Don't floor it.

397
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:58,039
Be careful.

398
00:15:58,039 --> 00:15:59,200
This is so fast.

399
00:15:59,200 --> 00:15:59,960
Floor it.

400
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,159
It's okay. This one is not bad.

401
00:16:02,119 --> 00:16:02,400
No way.

402
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,599
I can't catch up with you.

403
00:16:03,599 --> 00:16:04,960
You're pretty bold with the gas pedal.

404
00:16:05,919 --> 00:16:07,679
You drifted a bit in the middle, right?

405
00:16:07,679 --> 00:16:08,039
Yes.

406
00:16:08,039 --> 00:16:09,119
I was scared.

407
00:16:09,119 --> 00:16:10,000
It just went

408
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:10,559
like this.

409
00:16:10,559 --> 00:16:10,919
Yes.

410
00:16:11,919 --> 00:16:12,760
Shall we continue?

411
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:14,039
Let's do a few more rounds.
You go ahead.

412
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,559
You even looked back at me?

413
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:28,640
Why did you keep looking back at me?

414
00:16:28,640 --> 00:16:30,200
I was checking if you overtook me.

415
00:16:30,496 --> 00:16:32,400
Not giving me the chance
to overtake you, huh?

416
00:16:37,719 --> 00:16:39,119
Not giving me the chance, huh?

417
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:40,960
I won't give you.

418
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:42,039
I won't give you the chance.

419
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,400
This path is too narrow.

420
00:16:46,559 --> 00:16:47,719
The path is too narrow.
You can't overtake me.

421
00:16:51,039 --> 00:16:52,679
I thought it was like

422
00:16:52,679 --> 00:16:53,880
the big-circle kind.

423
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:54,239
Yes.

424
00:16:56,719 --> 00:16:57,919
Not bad. Quite fun.

425
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:00,119
A bit more fun than archery.

426
00:17:00,119 --> 00:17:01,080
More fun than archery.

427
00:17:01,919 --> 00:17:03,919
It feels like there will be
a beautiful sunset today.

428
00:17:04,719 --> 00:17:06,359
If you were in a relationship,

429
00:17:06,839 --> 00:17:08,359
what do you think would be
the most romantic thing

430
00:17:08,359 --> 00:17:09,760
to do with your girlfriend?

431
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,079
I don't think there's one thing

432
00:17:12,079 --> 00:17:13,184
that's the most romantic to me.

433
00:17:13,184 --> 00:17:14,760
There can be a lot of things.

434
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:16,719
What would you like to do with her?

435
00:17:21,359 --> 00:17:22,640
Maybe going on trips

436
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:24,520
and seeing some...

437
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:26,359
Seeing something like...

438
00:17:26,359 --> 00:17:27,719
You mean meeting friends?

439
00:17:27,719 --> 00:17:28,640
No.

440
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:30,079
Honestly, I think

441
00:17:30,079 --> 00:17:31,719
bringing my girlfriend

442
00:17:31,719 --> 00:17:33,680
to meet my friends all the time

443
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:35,599
is pretty meaningless.

444
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:36,520
Really?

445
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:37,439
I feel that way.

446
00:17:37,439 --> 00:17:38,880
You wouldn't want

447
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:40,479
to introduce your friends to her

448
00:17:40,479 --> 00:17:41,520
and share with her.

449
00:17:42,199 --> 00:17:43,119
You think it's boring.

450
00:17:43,119 --> 00:17:44,680
I think that's a bit forced.

451
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:45,640
I mean, I will,

452
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:47,800
but I don't want to always do that.

453
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:48,359
I just think

454
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:49,640
it's meaningless.

455
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:50,160
I think

456
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:51,839
we can have more time alone

457
00:17:51,839 --> 00:17:53,079
to do other things.

458
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:55,040
Then what would you do?

459
00:17:55,839 --> 00:17:57,439
Maybe going on trips.

460
00:17:57,439 --> 00:17:59,920
We'll go see places

461
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:01,959
we've never been to before.

462
00:18:01,959 --> 00:18:03,520
I will feel really good.

463
00:18:06,439 --> 00:18:08,119
Shall we go back to the camp
and rest for a while?

464
00:18:08,119 --> 00:18:08,719
Sure.

465
00:18:13,280 --> 00:18:14,319
It wore me out.

466
00:18:17,839 --> 00:18:18,239
What's up?

467
00:18:19,119 --> 00:18:20,119
What do you want?

468
00:18:26,117 --> 00:18:27,424
(Childlike)

469
00:18:29,959 --> 00:18:30,464
Look at me.

470
00:18:30,464 --> 00:18:30,959
Come on.

471
00:18:30,959 --> 00:18:31,800
Look at me and laugh silly.

472
00:18:32,439 --> 00:18:33,760
(Looking bewildered)
Laugh silly.

473
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:34,479
Who's silly? I'm laughing silly?

474
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:36,520
Who else could it be?

475
00:18:37,439 --> 00:18:38,599
Okay, fine.

476
00:18:45,719 --> 00:18:47,079
Why can't I ride it?

477
00:18:48,359 --> 00:18:49,520
I'm waiting for you to ride it.

478
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:50,400
I'll take photos of you.

479
00:18:53,439 --> 00:18:53,800
It moved.

480
00:18:54,586 --> 00:18:56,352
(Walking instead of riding)

481
00:19:01,079 --> 00:19:02,119
Handsome.

482
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:05,800
Do I look like something out of Saw?

483
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:07,520
There's a clown riding a tricycle in it.

484
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,160
Really?

485
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,488
- Yes.
- I don't watch horror movies.

486
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:12,599
You haven't seen that?

487
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:15,319
That was a childhood trauma for me.

488
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:22,560
Fishing?

489
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:23,920
We can go check it out.

490
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:26,199
Have you ever gone fishing?

491
00:19:26,839 --> 00:19:27,520
No.

492
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:28,400
I think it takes forever.

493
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,439
I can't really sit still.

494
00:19:30,119 --> 00:19:30,800
I mean,

495
00:19:31,479 --> 00:19:32,640
now it might be better.

496
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:34,280
But when you were a kid,

497
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:36,520
if you were asked to sit

498
00:19:36,520 --> 00:19:38,280
in one place for more than 30 minutes...

499
00:19:38,839 --> 00:19:39,680
You can't do it?

500
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:40,800
Right. Can you sit still?

501
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:41,760
I can.

502
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:43,319
I can even sit for three hours.

503
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:44,160
Indeed.

504
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:45,560
You and your sewing machine.

505
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:47,000
- Sewing machine master.
- Always stepping on it, right?

506
00:19:49,119 --> 00:19:50,079
Come on, you use the red one.

507
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:51,079
Happy.

508
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:54,599
Be careful.

509
00:19:56,134 --> 00:19:56,800
(Rod blank)

510
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:57,719
I forgot to open this.

511
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:02,280
It seems like you have to do this first.

512
00:20:02,959 --> 00:20:04,119
Put it underneath.

513
00:20:05,119 --> 00:20:06,839
Then you have to pull it.

514
00:20:07,239 --> 00:20:08,760
After that...

515
00:20:12,040 --> 00:20:12,520
(Successful cast)
Right?

516
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:14,760
Yes, I think that's how it is.

517
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:16,479
You try it.

518
00:20:16,479 --> 00:20:16,959
Give it a try.

519
00:20:18,119 --> 00:20:18,880
Be careful.

520
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:19,839
I can't cast accurately.

521
00:20:19,839 --> 00:20:21,160
- Okay.
- Get behind me.

522
00:20:21,824 --> 00:20:22,336
Wait.

523
00:20:22,336 --> 00:20:23,264
Get behind me.

524
00:20:24,439 --> 00:20:25,319
When the time comes...

525
00:20:26,959 --> 00:20:27,800
This is good.

526
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:28,319
This is cool.

527
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:31,439
Right, you're so smart.

528
00:20:31,439 --> 00:20:32,599
That's exactly it.

529
00:20:34,719 --> 00:20:35,119
Like this.

530
00:20:38,439 --> 00:20:39,760
Got that feeling, right?

531
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:48,864
(Shot by Wang Yi)

532
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:51,119
Okay.

533
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:54,839
Now, in this kind of situation,

534
00:20:54,839 --> 00:20:55,800
you just set up a stand,

535
00:20:56,280 --> 00:20:57,479
and then start fiddling with the phone.

536
00:20:57,664 --> 00:20:58,640
(Waiting for the fish to take the bait)

537
00:20:58,640 --> 00:21:00,119
Sitting and waiting
for the fish to take the bait, right?

538
00:21:00,119 --> 00:21:02,319
But you need to reel it in,

539
00:21:02,319 --> 00:21:04,119
as you've let out too much line.

540
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:05,280
Reel it in.

541
00:21:06,599 --> 00:21:08,839
I need to clip it up a bit.

542
00:21:09,439 --> 00:21:09,880
Okay.

543
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:11,040
Yes, it seems like it.

544
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:11,520
Right.

545
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:12,160
You need to...

546
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:14,040
Then you reel it in.

547
00:21:16,239 --> 00:21:17,520
Yeah, you're so smart.

548
00:21:17,856 --> 00:21:19,648
(Compliment mode activated)

549
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:20,800
Yeah, you're so smart.

550
00:21:21,376 --> 00:21:22,280
You are flattering me.

551
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:23,400
I can't take it.

552
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,760
Your bait is still in London right now.

553
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:27,160
You need to reel it in.

554
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:27,479
Okay.

555
00:21:27,584 --> 00:21:28,640
If you're in Beijing

556
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:30,400
by yourself,

557
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:31,599
the fishing line is too far for you.

558
00:21:33,119 --> 00:21:33,400
Okay.

559
00:21:34,079 --> 00:21:34,839
Let's head towards

560
00:21:36,719 --> 00:21:38,239
Huangpu district.

561
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,040
Okay, that's about right.

562
00:21:46,079 --> 00:21:46,560
Okay.

563
00:21:46,839 --> 00:21:48,719
Wait, I need to reel it in.

564
00:21:49,959 --> 00:21:51,640
Where is this hook stuck?

565
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:52,719
(Hook's caught on the weeds)

566
00:21:52,719 --> 00:21:53,359
Wait, don't move.

567
00:21:54,319 --> 00:21:55,239
Be careful.

568
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:57,760
Watch your hands.

569
00:22:01,239 --> 00:22:01,959
So impressive.

570
00:22:02,272 --> 00:22:03,079
(Compliment anytime)

571
00:22:03,079 --> 00:22:05,319
You're great at solving problems.

572
00:22:06,319 --> 00:22:07,168
I just lifted it.

573
00:22:07,168 --> 00:22:08,199
Stop flattering me.

574
00:22:09,199 --> 00:22:10,560
You're getting shy from my compliments?

575
00:22:10,560 --> 00:22:11,319
I get shy easily.

576
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,079
Seems not.

577
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:15,560
Where are Mr. Dong and the others?

578
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:17,119
Should we go look for him?

579
00:22:17,119 --> 00:22:17,760
Sure.

580
00:22:19,119 --> 00:22:20,599
You know, I'm such a dork.

581
00:22:20,599 --> 00:22:23,200
Standing long jump is my worst sport.

582
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,040
I can only jump about one meter.

583
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:26,520
Then your...

584
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:28,640
So what do you think of my driving?

585
00:22:28,640 --> 00:22:29,800
I think your driving is fine.

586
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:31,000
You can already reverse

587
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,400
into a spot in one go.

588
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:34,976
You passed the road test
and the parking test on your first try.

589
00:22:34,976 --> 00:22:36,280
I respect that.

590
00:22:36,280 --> 00:22:36,959
I believe it.

591
00:22:36,959 --> 00:22:37,760
Thank you.

592
00:22:39,599 --> 00:22:40,079
There's a frisbee.

593
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:42,368
But you can throw it, right?

594
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:44,439
Spread out.

595
00:22:44,439 --> 00:22:45,400
Pass it in a star pattern?

596
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:46,560
Sure.

597
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:48,479
You guys can stand in a square
or star pattern.

598
00:22:48,479 --> 00:22:49,280
Count Xuan in.

599
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:52,119
Xuan, give it a try.

600
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:54,400
One, two, three, go!

601
00:22:57,760 --> 00:22:58,359
Sorry!

602
00:22:59,488 --> 00:23:00,520
I gave it to him.

603
00:23:04,480 --> 00:23:05,359
Great.

604
00:23:06,144 --> 00:23:07,479
Do whatever feels comfortable for you.

605
00:23:16,719 --> 00:23:17,800
Impressive.

606
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:34,135
(Skip to the next episode.
Next episode is more exciting)
